==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:John Locke|John Locke]] from the non-English language word ''séméiotikè'' which meant the art of [[musical notation]].

===Noun===
'''semiotics'''

# The study of [[sign]]s and [[symbol]]s, especially as means of [[language]] or [[communication]].

